---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ContactCard from '@components/profiles/ContactCard';
import CircleCard from '@components/common/CircleCard';
import style from '@src/pages/fuksis/fuksis.module.scss';
import boardStyle from '@components/profiles/Board.module.scss';
import ccStyle from '@components/common/CircleCard.module.scss';

import heropic from '@src/assets/images/20230502154358-1c055172-xx.jpg';
import fuksicaptain1 from '@src/assets/officials/2026/Milja_Janis.jpg';
import fuksicaptain2 from '@src/assets/officials/2026/Elsa_Kuntsi.jpg';

const description = 'Hi there, fuksi! Start by reading this.';

const data1 = {
  title: 'Fuksi Captain',
  name: 'Milja Jänis',
  email: 'fuksikapteeni@as.fi',
  telegram: 'kalavelho',
  picture: fuksicaptain1,
};

const data2 = {
  title: 'Fuksi Captain',
  name: 'Elsa Kuntsi',
  email: 'fuksikapteeni@as.fi',
  telegram: 'saippuamarja',
  picture: fuksicaptain2,
};

const styleCard = { '--profile-img-size': '20rem', marginBottom: '5rem' };
---

<BaseLayout
  title="For Fuksis"
  background={heropic}
  heroHeight="tall"
  description={description}
  lang="en"
  slug="/en/fuksis"
>
  <div>
    <br />
    <p>
    Hello new fuksi! Congratulations on your study place and a warm welcome to the Guild of Automation and Systems Technology! We are your Fuksi Captains Elsa and Milja, and our job is to support you in your fuksi year’s adventures towards your teekkari cap. All sorts of useful material will be gathered here throughout the summer to help you get started with your studies and support you through your whole first year. As the Fuksi Captains, we are the people you can reach out to whenever anything at all is bothering you, or even just for fun! 
    </p>
  </div>

  <div style={styleCard} class={boardStyle.board}>
    <ContactCard data={data1} />
    <ContactCard data={data2} />
  </div>
  <div>
    <p>
    Whether it’s something small or a big concern, we will answer and do our best to help. :)

    </p>
  </div>


  <h2 id="1" class="underline">Before the start of your studies</h2>

  <div class={style.cardlist}>
    <CircleCard
      title="Accept your study place"
      link="https://opintopolku.fi/konfo/en/sivu/how-to-accept-an-offer-of-admission-in-joint-application-to-higher-education"
    />
    <CircleCard
      title="Register to be present"
      link="https://www.aalto.fi/en/applications-instructions-and-guidelines/annual-enrolment"
    />
    <CircleCard
      title="Become a guild member"
      link="https://kide.app/memberships/9864c555-8dbe-40c8-9246-064ca682e587"
    />
    <CircleCard title="Apply for a student card" link="https://www.frank.fi/en/studentcard/" />
    <div class={ccStyle.badge}>
      Apply for housing through&nbsp;
      <a href="https://domo.ayy.fi/en" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"> AYY </a>
      &nbsp;or&nbsp;
      <a href="https://hoas.fi/en" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"> HOAS </a>
    </div>
    <CircleCard title="Apply for a study grant" link="https://www.kela.fi/opintotuki" />
    <CircleCard title="Get a HSL travel card" link="https://www.hsl.fi/en/tickets-and-fares/hsl-card" />
    <CircleCard title="Read the fuksiguide" link="./fuksis/fuksiguide" targetSelf />
    <CircleCard title="Join the AS fuksis Telegram group" link="./fuksis#Telegram" targetSelf />
  </div>

  <h3 id= "Orientaion">Orientation week and VarASlähtö</h3>
  <div>
      <p>
    Orientation week will be organised in the last week of August, 24.-28.8.. You should already mark this in your calendar! The eventful week starts on Monday the 24th of August at 9:00 with a delicious breakfast at the Undergraduate Centre (Otakaari 1).
    </p>
    <p>
    You have a chance to get a head start to the events of the fuksi year on Saturday the 15th of August starting at 14:00 on Alvari Square (Alvarinaukio), in Otaniemi. In VarASlähtö you can get to know fellow new fuksis, ISOs (tutors), and us already before orientation week. More information about VarASlähtö will be shared later on Telegram!
      </p>
  </div>


  <h3 id="Telegram">Telegram</h3>
  <div>
    <p>
    Telegram, known as “tg” among friends, is the most used app for communication in Otaniemi. Telegram is also used in our guild as an essential tool in giving out very important information to fuksis, and we hope that all fuksis join the Telegram group for <a href="https://t.me/+_mVvsclQIKsxOGQ0">AS bachelor fuksis</a> and DSD (Digital systems and design) fuksis also join the group for <a href="https://t.me/+P9iw4WYk4xMxN2Jk">DSD fuksis</a>. In addition, we recommend following the <a href="">announcements channel for AS bachelor fuksis</a>. All important information that you need to know will be sent to this channel, so that you won’t miss anything!
    </p>
  </div>

  <h3 id="Kilta">Guild and Fuksis</h3>
  <div>
    <p>
    AS guild is a special status association under AYY, uniting students of Automation and Robotics, Information Technology as well as Digital Systems and Design majors. The guild also includes students from other programmes who are interested in AS’s activities. AS organises many events for its members, advocates for them at the university’s bodies and cooperates with other student associations and companies.

    </p>
    <p>
    AS welcomes over 200 bachelor fuksis each year, whose integration into the guild is taken care of by the guild’s Fuksi Captains with help from the Masters and International Student Captains (MISCs), the ISOboss, DSDeputy and Fuksi aASistants. Together these form the guild’s Fuksi Committee, ASPU.

    </p>
    <p>
    ASPU is assisted by a large number of enthusiastic ISOs, whose job it is to support you throughout the whole year regarding anything to do with studies or student life. We have placed you in a fuksi group that consists of around 10 fuksis as well as a few ISOs. You will get to know your fuksi group in VarASlähtö and during the orientation week. All of ASPU and every ISO is here for you!


    </p>
  </div>

  <h3 id=lakkitutkinto"">Cap degree</h3>
  <div>
      <p>
    The tekkari cap is without a doubt the most important emblem of a teekkari, and not just anyone can wear it. You can receive your teekkari cap by completing the cap degree, whereupon you will get to put the cap on your head at the possible Wappu at exactly midnight.
      </p>
      <p>
    The contents of the cap degree are specified in the fuksi point card, which every fuksi will receive right at the beginning of the orientation week. Don’t worry if you can’t make it though – you can also get it later from the Captains. 
 
      </p>
      <p>
    Filling out the point card is a great opportunity to get to know everything that Aalto, AYY, the guilds, and Otaniemi in general have to offer. There’s no need to stress about the points, because it’s easy to get enough points for the cap degree, and when student life hooks you in, they seem to come from every direction!

      </p>
  </div>

  <h3 id="haalarit">Overalls</h3>
  <div>
      <p>
    Overalls are an outfit from which a Finnish student can be recognised. Every guild has overalls in their own signature colour. Students of AS have purple overalls that have a black sleeve with a white pocket, and an arduino-blue pocket on the thigh. You can order your own overalls during the orientation week. You can decorate your overalls to your liking, for example by sewing on overall patches. Remember that patches should be sewn on by hand!
      </p>
      <p>
      If you notice something wrong with the overalls, please report it immediately. Defects caused by manufacturing errors will be repaired. Not all parts, such as the buttons and the zipper, can withstand super heavy use, but they are quite easy to fix yourself. You can ask older guild members for tips!
      </p>
  </div>

  <h3 id="links">Useful links</h3>

  <div class={style.table}>
    <div class={style.list}>
      <h4 class={style.list__title}>STUDIES</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <a href="https://mycourses.aalto.fi/?lang=en" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"> MyCourses </a>{' '}
          (Here you can find information about courses)
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://sisu.aalto.fi/student/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"> Sisu </a>{' '}
          (Registration for courses, midterms and exams takes place here)
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.aalto.fi/en/school-of-electrical-engineering" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">
            School of Electrical Engineering
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://aalto.fi/en" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"> Aalto University </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.aalto.fi/en/student-guide" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"> Student guide </a>{' '}
          (Information and instructions about studies)
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.aalto.fi/en/services/aalto-space-mobile-application" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">
            Aalto Space application
          </a>{' '}
          (Reserve spaces for studying)
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class={style.list}>
      <h4 class={style.list__title}>HEALTH CARE</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.yths.fi/en/frontpage/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"> YTHS </a>
        </li>
        <li>Otaniemi: Otakaari 12</li>
        <li>Töölö: Töölönkatu 37 a</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class={style.list}>
      <h4 class={style.list__title}>TRANSPORT</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.hsl.fi/en" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"> HELSIKI REGION TRANSPORT </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.hsl.fi/en/tickets-and-fares/hsl-card" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"> Travel card </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://www.hsl.fi/en/tickets-and-fares/hsl-app" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">
            HSL application
          </a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class={style.list}>
      <h4 class={style.list__title}>EATING</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <a href="https://kanttiinit.fi/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"> Canteens </a>{' '}
          (student cafeteria menus)
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class={style.list}>
      <h4 class={style.list__title}>HOUSING</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <a href="https://ayyasunnot.fi/en/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"> AYY housing info </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://domo.ayy.fi/en" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"> Domo housing service (AYY) </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <a href="https://hoas.fi/en" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"> HOAS </a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
